    "what_description": "Zieria laxiflora is a shrub native to Australia, belonging to the family Rutaceae. It has a sprawling habit, growing up to 1 meter in height, with a spread of 1-2 meters. The leaves are dark green, linear to lance-shaped, 3-9 cm long, 1-3 mm wide, and have a blunt tip. The inflorescence is a compound corymb, composed of 2-5 cymules, each with 3-7 flowers, which are white, 4-6 mm long, and 4-merous. The fruit is a berry, green when immature, turning yellow when ripe, 6-8 mm long, and 6-8 mm wide.",
