    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Zieria laxiflora are exhibited through its ability to combat microbial infections, particularly exhibiting strong antimicrobial activity due to the presence of volatile oils and flavonoids, which contribute to its effectiveness in reducing oxidative stress and preventing cell damage, thereby showcasing its significant antioxidant properties. The plant also demonstrates anti-inflammatory properties by modulating the production of pro-inflammatory mediators, thus alleviating inflammation and associated symptoms. Furthermore, its antifungal properties are attributed to the presence of saponins and other bioactive compounds, which inhibit the growth of fungi and prevent the spread of fungal infections. Additionally, the antimicrobial and antifungal properties of Zieria laxiflora also translate to its antibacterial properties, where it inhibits the growth of bacteria and prevents the development of bacterial infections. The bioactive compounds present in the plant, including flavonoids, volatile oils, and saponins, are responsible for its medicinal properties.",
